    aMCPrompt += 'issues, risk of downtime). Generating a prediction model in ThingWorx Analytics can involve both training ';
    aMCPrompt += 'the model and validating it. Validation is the process by which a model is evaluated for the accuracy of ';
    aMCPrompt += 'the results it produces. Typically, the training process runs on a subset of "training" data, which is ';
    aMCPrompt += 'usually 80% of records in the original dataset. Validation typically occures on the "validation" data, or ';
    aMCPrompt += 'the remaining 20% of records in the original dataset. Sometimes the a second validation is performed on ';
    aMCPrompt += 'the training data. Generally validation metrics are trustworthy when calculated on validation data. ';
    aMCPrompt += 'Validation metrics are generally lower when calculated on validation data, but if they are much lower, ';
    aMCPrompt += 'then that can indicate that the model is "overfitting" the training data. In this case, the model does ';
    aMCPrompt += 'not really understand the underlying trends and relationships in the data. ';
    var result = aMCPrompt;
