    aMJPrompt += 'and "FAILED". "startDateTime" is the time at which the Analytics Server started processing the job, ';
    aMJPrompt += 'not the time when the user submitted the job. "endDateTime" is the time at which the Analytics Server stopped ';
    aMJPrompt += 'processing the job. "runTime" is the amount of time the Analytics Server processed the job. ';
    aMJPrompt += '"jobName" is the name of the model job entered by the user.';
    aMJPrompt += '"jobDescription" is a description for the model job entered by the user. ';
    aMJPrompt += '"modelTJobId" is the model training job ID assigned by the ThingWorx Analytics Server. ';
    aMJPrompt += '"modelVTDJobId" is the ID of the model validation job run against training data. ';
    aMJPrompt += '"modelVVDJobId" is the ID of the model validation job run against validation data. ';
    aMJPrompt += '"datasetUri" is the URI of the dataset that was used to train and validate the model. ';
    aMJPrompt += '"goalName" is the field in the dataset that was the "goal", or outcome of interest, of the model. ';
    aMJPrompt += 'ThingWorx Analytics ingests and analyzes data. It uses a set of machine learning algorithms to ';
    aMJPrompt += 'identify meaningful patterns in the data. Based on this analysis of the existing data, a generalized ';
    aMJPrompt += 'prediction model is generated, or "trained". This model can then be applied to subsequent data to make ';
    aMJPrompt += 'predictions, called "scores", associated with specific outcomes (such as machine failures, performance ';
    aMJPrompt += 'issues, risk of downtime). Generating a prediction model in ThingWorx Analytics can involve both training ';
    aMJPrompt += 'the model and validating it. Validation is the process by which a model is evaluated for the accuracy of ';
    aMJPrompt += 'the results it produces. Typically, the training process runs on a subset of "training" data, which is ';
    aMJPrompt += 'usually 80% of records in the original dataset. Validation typically occures on the "validation" data, or ';
    aMJPrompt += 'the remaining 20% of records in the original dataset. Sometimes the a second validation is performed on ';
    aMJPrompt += 'the training data.  ';
    aMJPrompt += 'Here are the model training and jobs. ';
                                   
    let counter = 0;
    jobInfoPageValues.rows.toArray().forEach(row => {
        aMJPrompt += 'Model job  '+counter+' state: '+row.state+', ';
        aMJPrompt += ' startDateTime: '+row.startDateTime+', ';
        aMJPrompt += ' endDateTime: '+row.endDateTime+', ';
        aMJPrompt += ' runTime: '+row.runTime+', ';
        aMJPrompt += ' jobName: '+row.jobName+', ';
        aMJPrompt += ' jobDescription: '+row.jobDescription+', ';
        aMJPrompt += ' modelTJobId: '+row.modelTJobId+', ';
        aMJPrompt += ' modelVTDJobId: '+row.modelVTDJobId+', ';
        aMJPrompt += ' modelVVDJobId: '+row.modelVVDJobId+', ';
        aMJPrompt += ' datasetUri: '+row.datasetUri+', ';
